body_text.text:
The number of organizations with a CDP mandate in Canada declined slightly over time (280 in 2004; 267 in 2010). Despite this relative stability nationally, there were notable differences within several provinces (Appendix 3 – online file), likely related to restructuring of the public health infrastructure. Also the number of ‘user’ organizations declined, and half of the 10 provinces experienced declines in the number of ‘resource’ organizations (Fig. 1
). However, in every province, the number of organizations designated as ‘both’ increased. PE, NL and NS maintained the highest number of CDP organizations per 100,000 persons (Fig. 2
).
